              <title xml:lang="eng" type="desc"/>
              <incipit xml:lang="per"/>
              <explicit xml:lang="ara" defective="true"/>
              <note>An ethical miscellany in prose and verse after the style of the<title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Gulistān (<foreign xml:lang="per">گلستان</foreign>)</title>. The book is
                                divided into five chapters called āshyānah, each of which is further
                                subdivided into sections called parvāz</note>
              <note>This work, of which the present may be a unique copy, was composed
                                during the reign of<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/59940176" key="no98106664">Shāh ʻAbbas
                                    II (<date calendar="Hijri-qamari" from="1642" to="1667">1052-1077</date>)</persName>(see<locus n="116a">fol.
                                    116a</locus>), and therefore this manuscript, of which
                                unfortunately the first folio is missing, must have been written
                                during the author's lifetime</note>
              <listBibl>
                <bibl>For a more detailed description see Arberry 1939, page 387.</bibl>
                <bibl/>
              </listBibl>
              <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
